## Special Cases

### Multiple Authors

**1-2 authors**: List all
- "Smith and Jones [1]"
- "Smith, J.; Jones, A."

**3+ authors**: Use "et al."
- "Smith et al. [1]"
- "Smith, J.; Jones, A.; Lee, K.; et al."

**Threshold**: Typically 3+ authors, but check journal guidelines

### Same First Author, Same Year

{% if citation_style.format == 'Author-Year' %}
Use letters: `(Smith et al., 2024a)`, `(Smith et al., 2024b)`
{% else %}
Use separate numbers: `[1]`, `[2]`
{% endif %}

### Online Resources

**With DOI**:
```
Author, A. Title. Journal Name 2024, 123, 456. DOI: 10.1234/journal.2024.123456
```

**Without DOI (with URL)**:
```
Author, A. Title. Website Name. Available online: https://example.com (accessed on 1 January 2024).
```

### Preprints

```
Author, A. Title. Preprint Server 2024. DOI: 10.1234/preprint.2024.123456
```

## Citation Management

### Consistency Checks

- [ ] All in-text citations have corresponding references
- [ ] All references are cited in text
- [ ] Citation format is consistent throughout
- [ ] Author names are formatted consistently
- [ ] Journal abbreviations follow standard (if applicable)
- [ ] DOIs are included (if required)

### Common Errors to Avoid

1. **Inconsistent format**: Mixing `[1]` and `(Smith, 2024)`
2. **Missing citations**: References without in-text citations
3. **Orphan citations**: In-text citations without references
4. **Incorrect author names**: Typos or inconsistent spelling
5. **Missing information**: Incomplete reference details

## Journal-Specific Guidelines

**Important**: Always check target journal's author guidelines for:
- Citation style (Numeric/Author-Year/Superscript)
- Reference list format
- Author name format (initials vs. full names)
- Journal name abbreviations
- DOI requirements
- Maximum reference count

